Product Title: e.l.f. Cosmetics All Over Color Stick - Pink Lemonade
Review Date: 2017/03/09
Store: e.l.f.
Product Description: ['New Instantly Brightens Eyes, Lips and Face Naturally Illuminates for a Healthy Glow Instantly Soothes & Conditions Skin Multi-Purpose Formula Safe, Gentle Formula Instantly beautiful, healthy-looking skin designed, formulated and tested by our professional team of makeup artists.']
Average Rating: 4.1
Product Details: {'Is Discontinued By Manufacturer': 'No', 'Product Dimensions': '2 x 2 x 3 inches; 0.8 Ounces', 'Date First Available': 'May 14, 2009', 'Manufacturer': 'E.L.F. Cosmetics'}
Review Text: This is a pretty color but I bought this blush based on the ingredients shown in the picture on the back of the package which have a low toxic rating. HOWEVER the product I received has a different ingredient list that includes BHA which according to the Skin Deep website is a Human endocrine disruptor - strong evidence. As well as petrolatum classified as expected to be toxic or harmful  This also has proplyparaben a Human immune toxicant or allergen - strong evidence.  So I'm not sure I should use it which is a waste of money.  It rates an overall moderate toxic level according to EWG.
Review Title: Moderately Toxic
Rating: 3.0
--------------------------------------------------

Product Title: Jade Rose Quartz Roller for Face 2 in 1 Gua Sha Set Including Rose Quartz Roller and Jade Face Massager 100% Real Natural Jade Facial Roller Anti Aging Face Roller Massager by Rayfarmo
Review Date: 2019/03/22
Store: RAYFARMO
Average Rating: 4.3
Product Details: {'Is Discontinued By Manufacturer': 'No', 'Product Dimensions': '6 x 2 x 0.5 inches; 7.04 Ounces', 'UPC': '680727935887', 'Manufacturer': 'RAYFARMO'}

Store: KPOKPO
Average Rating: 4.0

SUMMARY:
The purchase history reflects a preference for multifunctional beauty and grooming products that focus on skin health and wellness, often leaning towards natural or low-toxicity options. The consistent ratings indicate a positive sentiment towards items that provide visible benefits, particularly in skincare tools (e.g., rollers, scrubbers), though there is skepticism towards specific ingredient safety, as evidenced by concerns about toxicity.

Common themes showcase a preference for products with soothing and massaging properties that contribute to relaxation and skin rejuvenation. Performance is often prioritized, notably in exfoliating and body care items, which receive higher ratings when effectiveness meets convenience.

Quality is important, as seen in the high ratings for well-reviewed massage and bath tools, yet there is moderate price sensitivity; for example, products with functional designs or better materials tend to perform better in reviews. Negative feedback arises from issues related to product efficacy and ingredient transparency, leading to lower scores for those perceived as underperforming or potentially harmful.

In conclusion, the core preferences suggest a strong inclination towards effective, safe, and versatile beauty and grooming products, with an emphasis on holistic skincare practices that promote a healthy and rejuvenated appearance.
